This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Obama on June 25, 2013, regarding power sector carbon pollution standards. The memorandum emphasizes the urgency of addressing climate change and reducing carbon pollution. It highlights the Environmental Protection Agency's (EPA) efforts in setting standards for carbon pollution from the transportation sector and directs the EPA to propose new standards for carbon pollution from power plants. The memorandum also calls for the use of market-based instruments, performance standards, and other regulatory flexibilities to reduce costs and ensure the continued provision of reliable and affordable electric power. It concludes with general provisions on the implementation of the memorandum.